=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Mono-Boc protect ethylenediamine to give N-Boc-ethylenediamine, BocNHCH2CH2NH2. | Step 2: Sulfonylate the free amine with 2-pyridinesulfonyl chloride (base, e.g. Et3N/CH2Cl2) to form BocNHCH2CH2NHSO2(2-pyridyl). | Step 3: N-Alkylate the sulfonamide with cyclohexylmethyl bromide (BrCH2C6H11; e.g. NaH or K2CO3 in DMF) to give BocNHCH2CH2N(CH2C6H11)SO2(2-pyridyl). | Step 4: Remove Boc (TFA or HCl/dioxane) to obtain H2NCH2CH2N(CH2C6H11)SO2(2-pyridyl). | Step 5: React this primary amine with 4-fluorobenzonitrile under SNAr conditions (DIPEA or K2CO3, DMF, heat) to replace F and furnish the exact target N#Cc1ccc(NCCN(CC2CCCCC2)S(=O)(=O)c2ccccn2)cc1.

